 high costs and reporting headaches. By investing through an IRA, you can a=
void those headaches. Alto makes money by charging 1% annually on the accou=
nt balance to cover custody, insurance, and cold storage costs, and a 1.5% =
fee for each transaction.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Alto is able to deliver a Self =
Directed IRA product at a much lower cost than incumbents because it&#8217;=
s built from the ground up on new technology, including direct integrations=
 with alternative investment platforms, which gives it a lower cost structu=
re than incumbents. As a result, Alto doesn&#8217;t charge based on the siz=
e of your account or investments; it charges an annual flat fee and flat pe=
r-investment fees. There are two account types (in addition to Crypto):&nbs=
p;</p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5=
